    *numbers: Iterable[Number], multiple: int = 2
) -&gt; Union[int, Tuple[int, ...]]
</code></pre> <p>Round to the nearest multiple of 2, returns a single value or a tuple of values</p> Source code in <code>Broken/Core/BrokenResolution.py</code> Python<pre><code>@staticmethod
def round(*numbers: Iterable[Number], multiple: int=2) -&gt; Union[int, Tuple[int, ...]]:
    """Round to the nearest multiple of 2, returns a single value or a tuple of values"""
    values = tuple(max(multiple, multiple*round(value/multiple)) for value in numbers)
    return (values[0] if (len(values) == 1) else values)
